ArrayList :

1. ArrayList is not synchronized.
2. ArrayList increments 50% of the current array size.
3. ArrayList is not a legacy class. Introduced in JDK 1.2
4. ArrayList is fast because it is non-synchronized.
5. ArrayList uses theIterator interface to traverse the elements.


Vector :

1. Vector is synchronized.
2. Vector increments 100%, doubles the array size.
3. Vector is a legacy class.
4. Vector is slow as it is synchronized i.e., in multithreading environment,
it holds the other threads in a runnable or non-runnable state until the current
thread releases the lock of the object.
5. Vector can use Iterator interface or Enumeration interface to traverse the elements.
